natspec.details: This contract is instantiated for each project and can be edited for individual needs.

acceptBuilderJoinRequest(address).notice: Already accepted builder can accept new builder.

acceptNode(bytes[112]).notice: Accepting first request in the stack

params.secret: sharing encrypted common secret for nodes TODO: Secret should be updated as hash of previous secret So that the node doesn't have access to previous models TODO: Should not accept node when plan is running

addBuilder(address,bytes32).notice: Already accepted builder can add new builder.

constructor.details: Initializes the project. Creator becomes both builder and data provider, might be changed in future

params.secret: - Encrypted secret for the owner (owner encrypts for himself)

params.reward: - reward for data providers for each model submitted

deactivate().details: onlyNode modifier is not required. It is checked inside _deactivateNode(...)

declineBuilderJoinRequest(address).notice: Already accepted builder can accept new builder.

declineNode().notice: Declining first request in the stack

isNode(address).notice: Check if given address belongs to node

requestJoinBuilder(bytes32).notice: Anyone can request to become a builder.

requestJoinNode(bytes32).notice: Node can request to join providing their public key.

setBuilderPublickey(bytes32).notice: Builder can update his public key.

natspec.notice: Project Contract manages references to Data Providers (nodes) and Builders (scientists). Data providers must watch this contract and execute new plans. Builders creat training plans.
